31:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who should NOT lead raids</span><hr size=1> If I'm uninformed about something that I feel I need to know, I don't sit there like an idiot and blame it on a raid leader. It's my own fault if I'm stupid, not a raid leader.<br>
<br>
If you feel you know something the raid leader doesn't, inform them...don't get all pissed because you failed to inform someone on tactics, loot rules, mobs, etc....it was your choice to go on a raid.<br>
<br>
What good is a good raid leader with crappy players? A raid n00b can ruin any raid. Loot whores can ruin any raid. <br>
<br>
You say you're seeing a lot of people who don't know how to lead dragon raids leading them nowadays...so where are all the people that know how? Do you know how? If you know how, why aren't you willing to contribute to the raid? If you don't know how, why question someone who's actually doing it? It's not like you did anything.<br>
<br>
Communication goes two ways, if you're sitting around expecting someone to tell you what's going on, it won't happen all the time.<br>
<br>
Your post should say &quot;People who should NOT raid&quot; too, there's tons of people who just go, who can't pull their weight, who fail to even show up for something they signed up for, who bitch over loot, who harrass the raid leader.<br>
<br>
When things like that happen, people always look for someone to string up by the neck...and for some reason it's always the raid leader, always responsible for idiots actions.<br>
<br>
You can't always expect the raid leader to hold your hand when they still have training wheels themself. <br>
<br>
For some reason all people can do is complain about it, instead of doing something about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utellwar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TellWar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/2/01 8:24:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who should NOT lead raids</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Easily solved, don't go on their raids. Make sure whatever you decide or work out before hand is made clear to all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
